    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - 13 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RT-6613 SERIES - INSTALL
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>INSTALL</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="4">
            <title>RIGHT REVERSE IDLER GEAR ASSEMBLY</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the needle bearing in the bore of the gear (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f13030l5">Figure 215</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f13030l5" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g13030l5" filename="../figg13/g13030l5.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 214. Install Needle Bearing on Bore of Gear</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Slide the thrust washer into position on the rear of the case boss and hold the gear
                    behind the washer (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f13030l6">Figure 216</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f13030l6" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g13030l6" filename="../figg13/g13030l6.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 215. Slide Thrust Washer into Position on Rear of Case Boss</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Make sure the roll pin is in place in the large diameter of the idler shaft and insert
                    the shaft through the gear, washer and boss, aligning the roll pin with the notch in the rear case
                    bore (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f13030l7">Figure 217</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f13030l7" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g13030l7" filename="../figg13/g13030l7.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 216. Insert Idler Shaft Through Gear, Washer and Boss</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Secure the shaft with the washer and elastic stop nut (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f13030l8">Figure 218</hotlnk>). Tighten to 50 to 60 ft-lbs. (68 to 81 N&#183;m).
                </para>
                <figure id="f13030l8" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g13030l8" filename="../figg13/g13030l8.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 217. Secure Shaft With Washer and Elastic Stop Nut</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
